== Prequisites

* Java 1.6
* MongoDB 1.4.3

== Configure MongoDB
To start MongoDB with just one instance (without replication), simply run:
  mongod
(see http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Tutorial for more details on how to start MongoDB)
If you intend to have 2 instances of MongoDB, a Master-Master relication structure may be suitable. In this case run the following command on both servers:
  mongod --master --slave --source <ip of the other server>
(see http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Master+Master+Replication for more details on Master-Master replication)

== Config Comy

Edit config.properties properly.

== Run

To run with memory in the range 2GB to 6GB:
java -server -Xms2000m -Xmx6000m -cp /comy.jar server /path/to/config.properties

== Remove old data

Schedule this to be run periodically (on Linux, use on crontab  etc.):
java -jar comy.jar gc /path/to/config.properties
